cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper proposes an approach for semantic relation classification, which is a common task in natural language processing and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed approach uses a combination of a large commonsense knowledge base and machine learning techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of a distributional navigational algorithm, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper proposes a sequence classification approach, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE).
